## Code Comments (CRITICAL — stop doing this)

- Prefer no comment over a long one. Code should be self-explanatory.
- One short line per comment; no paragraph-style or multi-sentence docblocks for obvious logic.
- If something needs more than 150 characters, refactor the code or put the explanation in the PR/commit — not in source.
- Applies to `//` and `/* */` comments in TypeScript/TSX.
